      "map_id": 34728742,
      "difficulty_level": "intermediate",
      "subjects_id": [],
      "solution": "Correct Answer (B) When the bile is diverted from the intestinal tract so that only the distal 50 to 100 cm of ileum is used for bile reabsorption,the procedure is known as biliopancreatic diversion. Most effective bariatric surgery,especially valuable in patients with severe morbid obesity or in those who have failed to maintain weight loss following gastric bypass surgery or restrictive procedures. Main side effect with BPD:Patient usually have an increase of 2-4 bowel movements/day, which in general are more malodorous, suggesting fat malabsorption. Due to the extreme malabsorption these operations produce there is a need for a high protein intake of around 90 g/day which many patients find difficult. If this is not achieved then protein calorie malnutrition can be a problem.",
